div.h1: User vs. Kernel Page Directories: Memory Isolation

div.p: Key insight: Kernel pages mapped in every process, but U/S=0 prevents user code from reading kernel memory.
U/S=1 in PTE Ring 3 U/S bit ACCESS GRANTED
U/S=0 in PTE Ring 3 < U/S bit PAGE FAULT (#PF)
U/S=0 in PTE Ring 0 U/S bit ACCESS GRANTED
U/S=1 in PTE Ring 0 U/S bit ACCESS GRANTED (Kernel can access all)
